WEBVTT

00:01.569 --> 00:02.568
<i> - Previously on "You"...</i>

00:02.670 --> 00:05.037
- Joe Goldberg? I heard
about you and Candace.

00:05.139 --> 00:07.506
- She thought she could be
happier with some guy in Rome.

00:07.608 --> 00:09.708
<i> Peach doesn't go anywhere</i>
<i> without that laptop.</i>

00:09.810 --> 00:12.811
<i> If only I could see inside.</i>

00:12.913 --> 00:14.980
<i> Guinevere Beck?</i>

00:15.082 --> 00:16.682
<i> This is the work</i>
<i> of a sick mind.</i>

00:16.784 --> 00:18.517
<i> She's obsessed with you.</i>

00:18.619 --> 00:20.886
<i> She wants you all to herself.</i>

00:20.988 --> 00:24.723
- It is exhausting
being your friend.

00:24.825 --> 00:26.558
- I don't need to love
your self-absorbed poetry

00:26.660 --> 00:27.893
in order to be kind to you.

00:27.995 --> 00:30.162
Beck rarely knows
what's best for her.

00:30.264 --> 00:31.830
<i> - I couldn't agree more.</i>

00:31.932 --> 00:33.565
<i> It's freeing, in a way,</i>
<i> to know for certain</i>

00:33.667 --> 00:35.267
<i> what I have to do</i>
<i> to protect you.</i>

00:35.369 --> 00:36.435
[blow lands]

00:36.537 --> 00:37.936
Paco, what did you do?

00:38.039 --> 00:39.271
- I didn't know
how many sleeping pills

00:39.373 --> 00:41.006
would knock him out.

00:41.108 --> 00:43.409
- [gagging, retching]

00:43.511 --> 00:45.344
[grunts]
- [groaning]

00:48.282 --> 00:49.548
Hey, you.

00:49.650 --> 00:50.916
<i> - Peach was attacked</i>

00:51.018 --> 00:53.352
in Central Park
in broad daylight.

00:53.454 --> 00:54.853
<i> I'm headed to the ER now.</i>

00:54.955 --> 00:56.855
- She's alive?

00:56.957 --> 00:58.824
<i> [tense music]</i>

01:00.494 --> 01:02.261
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

01:02.363 --> 01:04.696
<i> It's been three whole days</i>
<i> since I've seen you.</i>

01:04.799 --> 01:06.598
<i> I failed you, Beck,</i>

01:06.700 --> 01:08.534
<i> and this is my punishment.</i>

01:08.636 --> 01:10.602
<i> Is this my walk</i>
<i> to the gallows?</i>

01:10.704 --> 01:13.205
<i> Should I be preparing</i>
<i> last words?</i>

01:13.307 --> 01:15.808
<i> Some humans, Beck,</i>
<i> are cancer.</i>

01:15.910 --> 01:18.110
<i> Peach is Stage IV metastatic.</i>

01:18.212 --> 01:20.813
<i> I tried to cut out the mess</i>
<i> before it consumed you,</i>

01:20.915 --> 01:24.416
<i> but now, best case,</i>
<i> got to go in there</i>

01:24.518 --> 01:26.919
<i> and win an Oscar</i>
<i> kissing the ring.</i>

01:27.021 --> 01:29.154
<i> Worst case:</i>

01:29.256 --> 01:31.123
<i> she knows it was me</i>

01:31.225 --> 01:33.225
<i> and it's over.</i>

01:33.327 --> 01:36.895
<i> Is this an ambush?</i>
<i> Will you love me in prison?</i>

01:36.997 --> 01:38.330
[intercom buzzes]

01:38.999 --> 01:40.799
- Hi.
[gasps]

01:40.901 --> 01:41.900
Oh, no.

01:44.905 --> 01:47.773
[sighs] I can't believe
I told you

01:47.875 --> 01:49.641
to get involved
with your neighbor's shit.

01:49.743 --> 01:51.643
- It's okay.
It's not your fault.

01:51.745 --> 01:53.245
<i> God, I've missed you.</i>

01:53.347 --> 01:54.446
How's Peach?

01:54.548 --> 01:57.783
- Oh, as well
as can be expected.

01:57.885 --> 02:00.252
Um, do you mind
taking off your shoes

02:00.354 --> 02:03.655
and anything that has touched
other people or the subway?

02:03.757 --> 02:05.257
- Sure.

02:05.359 --> 02:08.026
[indistinct chatter]

02:12.700 --> 02:15.567
<i> [soft piano music]</i>

02:15.669 --> 02:22.708
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:26.580 --> 02:27.880
How are you feeling, Peach?

02:31.752 --> 02:33.218
- I'm onto you.

02:33.320 --> 02:35.187
- Hmm?

02:35.289 --> 02:38.724
<i> Is this it?</i>
<i> The noose tightening?</i>

02:38.826 --> 02:41.360
- You play the gormless
ne'er-do-well, and yet...

02:41.462 --> 02:43.729
- And yet?
- It was you.

02:45.466 --> 02:49.835
You're the one that warned me.
I have a stalker.

02:49.937 --> 02:51.837
<i> - Ha!</i>
Oh.

02:51.939 --> 02:53.539
- We're trying to figure out
who it is.

02:53.641 --> 02:55.807
You know, they say
most people are stalked

02:55.910 --> 02:58.076
by someone they know.

02:58.179 --> 02:59.845
- I mean,
isn't that terrifying?

02:59.947 --> 03:01.346
It's like I'm finally
understanding

03:01.448 --> 03:03.015
the dark side of celebrity.

03:03.117 --> 03:06.485
- This beauty blogger I know
is on her third stalker.

03:06.587 --> 03:08.554
- Becks,
I'd love some more tea.

03:08.656 --> 03:11.089
<i> - Oh, my shackled Cinderella,</i>
<i> if Peach gets her way,</i>

03:11.192 --> 03:12.724
<i> you'll be making organic...</i>
- Sure.

03:12.826 --> 03:14.092
<i> - Concussion tonic</i>
<i> until your beauty fades.</i>

03:14.195 --> 03:15.861
- Oh, um, do you want some?

03:15.963 --> 03:18.430
It'll be good for your head.
- I'm okay, thank you.

03:18.532 --> 03:20.065
<i> You have pages due.</i>

03:20.167 --> 03:21.533
<i> You have a boyfriend</i>
<i> with a black eye.</i>

03:21.635 --> 03:23.402
<i> None of this is okay.</i>

03:28.008 --> 03:29.675
Actually, I'm gonna...

03:32.813 --> 03:34.780
<i>- Why is he here?</i>

03:34.882 --> 03:36.682
- Hey, how long
is she gonna stay here?

03:36.784 --> 03:40.252
- I don't know.
Maybe indefinitely.

03:40.354 --> 03:43.355
She's afraid to stay at
her house, which I understand.

03:43.457 --> 03:45.023
[water pouring]

03:45.125 --> 03:47.759
- They let her out
of the hospital pretty quick.

03:47.861 --> 03:50.762
You know, like, three days?
I mean, it was a concussion.

03:50.864 --> 03:53.799
I don't think she should be
your responsibility.

03:53.901 --> 03:55.267
- Hey.

03:55.369 --> 03:58.070
When this is all over,
let's go away somewhere,

03:58.172 --> 04:00.205
just you and me.

04:00.307 --> 04:02.040
- I'm sorry to interrupt.

04:02.142 --> 04:04.042
- No, it's fine.
What's up?

04:04.144 --> 04:06.144
- Just, you know,
given everything

04:06.247 --> 04:08.280
that I've been through,

04:08.382 --> 04:11.316
male energy
in my healing space just...

04:11.418 --> 04:12.784
isn't optimal.

04:14.154 --> 04:17.422
Would you mind asking
Joseph to leave us?

04:17.524 --> 04:19.591
- I think he heard you, Peach.

04:19.693 --> 04:21.893
- I don't need confrontation
right now.

04:21.996 --> 04:24.396
Oh, and have him
take his gift with him.

04:32.539 --> 04:34.373
- I got to run some errands.

04:36.176 --> 04:37.643
- [whispering] I'm sorry.

04:39.947 --> 04:42.714
- Uh, Beck, my tea.

04:42.816 --> 04:44.549
- [sighs]

05:04.705 --> 05:07.773
<i> - Paris.</i>
<i> Two tickets, first class.</i>

05:07.875 --> 05:09.207
<i> I underestimated her.</i>

05:09.310 --> 05:10.876
<i> She's not thinking</i>
<i> about me at all.</i>

05:10.978 --> 05:13.045
<i> She's busy making you</i>
<i> all hers forever,</i>

05:13.147 --> 05:15.781
<i> and I put you</i>
<i> right in her pocket,</i>

05:15.883 --> 05:17.783
<i> where you can't write,</i>
<i> you can't love.</i>

05:17.885 --> 05:19.351
<i> You can't be you</i>

05:19.453 --> 05:21.019
<i> if you're living for Peach.</i>

05:21.121 --> 05:22.487
<i> I won't let it happen.</i>

05:22.589 --> 05:24.356
<i> I need a new plan.</i>

05:27.261 --> 05:29.561
<i> Because now</i>

05:29.663 --> 05:31.163
<i> it's war.</i>

05:31.265 --> 05:34.132
<i> [tense music]</i>

05:34.234 --> 05:40.539
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:47.681 --> 05:49.114
- Hey, Joe.

05:50.984 --> 05:53.552
- Oh.
- I'm so sorry, Joe.

05:53.654 --> 05:55.253
- It's okay.
It's--[chuckles]

05:55.356 --> 05:57.656
It's okay. We're good.
We're good, I promise.

05:57.758 --> 05:59.391
- Go inside,<i> mi'jo.</i>

06:09.470 --> 06:11.036
Just a little something
to say thank you.

06:11.138 --> 06:12.537
It's specialty.
Fudge brownies.

06:12.639 --> 06:14.506
- Oh, thank you.

06:14.608 --> 06:15.841
- It's kind of you
to get involved.

06:15.943 --> 06:17.342
I know things have been

06:17.444 --> 06:19.411
a little bumpy here
the past few weeks.

06:19.513 --> 06:21.179
<i> - Try months.</i>

06:21.281 --> 06:25.117
- I just want you to know
that we're working on it.

06:25.219 --> 06:28.754
So if you're thinking of
pressing charges or anything...

06:28.856 --> 06:31.056
<i> - And expose Paco's little</i>
<i> chemistry experiment? No.</i>

06:31.158 --> 06:32.290
Claudia.
- This whole experience

06:32.393 --> 06:34.192
really did something to Ron.

06:34.294 --> 06:36.294
And I know how it sounds,
but I feel like it changed him,

06:36.397 --> 06:38.263
like he wants to do better.

06:38.365 --> 06:40.699
- People don't change.

06:42.302 --> 06:44.569
And I'm not gonna
press charges.

06:44.671 --> 06:47.172
- Thank you, Joe.

06:47.274 --> 06:48.673
I owe you one.

06:57.084 --> 06:58.316
[bells jingle]

07:01.555 --> 07:03.455
- Hey.
- I got a minute.

07:03.557 --> 07:05.290
Peach is getting
an IV vitamin treatment

07:05.392 --> 07:08.493
across town,
but I wanted to see you.

07:08.595 --> 07:10.462
- Is everything okay?

07:10.564 --> 07:14.733
- Listen, I'm going away
for a few days.

07:14.835 --> 07:17.602
Peach's family has
a place in Greenwich,

07:17.704 --> 07:19.571
and she said she'd
feel safer there.

07:19.673 --> 07:21.440
<i> - I bet she would.</i>

07:21.542 --> 07:23.642
And what about school?
<i> What about us?</i>

07:23.744 --> 07:25.110
- Joe, she almost died.

07:25.212 --> 07:26.711
<i> - But not quite.</i>

07:28.582 --> 07:30.816
I know you've been
through a lot,

07:30.918 --> 07:32.851
but risking your future
for the same person

07:32.953 --> 07:34.753
who tried to sabotage
your career,

07:34.855 --> 07:38.056
like, a week ago,
I mean, it's a little crazy.

07:39.793 --> 07:43.128
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

07:43.230 --> 07:45.697
But I'm always gonna be honest
with you, and honestly...

07:48.135 --> 07:50.202
She's manipulating you.

07:50.304 --> 07:51.770
- Why in the world
would she want to--

07:51.872 --> 07:54.940
- Because--you really
can't see this?

07:55.042 --> 07:57.776
If you become your own person,

07:57.878 --> 07:59.511
she won't be able
to control you.

08:01.882 --> 08:03.281
I know that you don't
want to hear it,

08:03.383 --> 08:06.551
but the suicide attempt
was a show.

08:06.653 --> 08:08.487
She was never
in any real danger.

08:08.589 --> 08:11.289
- Oh, so she just
attacked herself in the park?

08:11.391 --> 08:13.191
- No, no, I'm not saying that.

08:13.293 --> 08:15.026
- Good, because
the whole victim blaming

08:15.128 --> 08:16.928
is starting to sound
a little 4chan.

08:19.466 --> 08:21.066
- Yeah. I...

08:24.238 --> 08:25.370
She's in love with you.

08:25.472 --> 08:27.539
You know that, right?

08:32.946 --> 08:34.746
- I got to go.
- Beck, no, I'm sorry.

08:34.848 --> 08:36.381
Wait. Wait.
- No, it's fine.

08:36.483 --> 08:38.250
Thank you for being honest.

08:39.753 --> 08:41.553
<i> - Okay, think.</i>

08:41.655 --> 08:43.822
<i> Peach is taking you</i>
<i> out of town.</i>

08:43.924 --> 08:45.891
<i> But that's just a prelude.</i>

08:45.993 --> 08:47.559
<i> She eases you into her world</i>

08:47.661 --> 08:49.728
<i> and then</i>
<i> snatches you away forever.</i>

08:49.830 --> 08:52.397
<i> I'd follow you, of course,</i>
<i> but, Beck, I hate French food.</i>

08:52.499 --> 08:54.366
<i> And you love New York,</i>
<i> and I need to save you.</i>

08:54.468 --> 08:56.201
<i> [groans]</i>
<i> My face is killing me.</i>

08:56.303 --> 08:58.570
<i> Thanks a billion, Ron.</i>

08:58.672 --> 09:01.840
<i> Okay, Greenwich.</i>
<i> That's where this stops.</i>

09:01.942 --> 09:03.842
<i> Connecticut's Gold Coast,</i>

09:03.944 --> 09:06.111
<i> land of hedge fund managers</i>
<i> and "Mayflower" descendants.</i>

09:06.213 --> 09:07.579
<i> Shouldn't be hard to find you.</i>

09:07.681 --> 09:09.114
<i> World gets a lot smaller</i>

09:09.216 --> 09:10.916
<i> when you only</i>
<i> have to search 1% of it.</i>

09:11.018 --> 09:14.185
<i> And just like that,</i>
<i> the Internet gods provide.</i>

09:14.288 --> 09:15.854
<i> Only an hour drive.</i>

09:15.956 --> 09:17.722
<i> I love a mini road trip.</i>

09:17.824 --> 09:20.625
<i> I used to take 'em</i>
<i> all the time with Candace.</i>

09:20.727 --> 09:24.563
<i> It'd be nice to make new,</i>
<i> happier memories, actually.</i>

09:24.665 --> 09:27.566
<i> [intense electronic music]</i>

09:27.668 --> 09:29.301
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:29.403 --> 09:31.303
<i> If I'm headed into 1% land,</i>

09:31.405 --> 09:33.605
<i> I'll need to look the part.</i>

09:33.707 --> 09:35.607
<i> So thank you, Benji.</i>

09:38.078 --> 09:39.711
<i> This is not how I lose you.</i>

09:39.813 --> 09:43.782
<i> No hesitation this time.</i>
<i> This time, I finish it.</i>

09:43.884 --> 09:45.383
<i> I'm coming, Beck.</i>
<i> I'm--</i>

09:45.485 --> 09:46.551
[tires screeching]

09:50.308 --> 09:52.208
[Pence's
<i> "Tonight You Belong to Me"]</i>

09:52.310 --> 09:54.410
<i> - ♪ I know ♪</i>

09:54.512 --> 10:00.817
<i> ♪ You belong to somebody new ♪</i>

10:00.919 --> 10:07.323
<i> ♪ But tonight</i>
<i> you belong to me ♪</i>

10:07.425 --> 10:09.725
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:09.828 --> 10:14.163
<i> ♪ Although we're apart ♪</i>

10:14.265 --> 10:18.534
<i> ♪ You're a part of my heart ♪</i>

10:18.636 --> 10:25.541
<i> ♪ And tonight</i>
<i> you belong to me ♪</i>

10:25.643 --> 10:26.876
- Candace.

10:26.978 --> 10:30.179
- Oh. Bunny.

10:30.281 --> 10:32.949
You okay?
[inhales sharply]

10:36.788 --> 10:38.521
- [groans]

10:42.627 --> 10:45.528
[breathing heavily]

10:45.630 --> 10:49.298
<i> [high-pitched ringing]</i>

10:49.400 --> 10:50.933
[groans]

10:53.938 --> 10:56.806
<i> [slow piano music]</i>

10:56.908 --> 11:03.913
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:29.707 --> 11:31.340
[siren blips]

11:49.427 --> 11:50.726
- Morning.

11:50.828 --> 11:53.296
- Morning.
- Car trouble?

11:53.398 --> 11:57.066
- No, no, no, but I--
- License and registration?

11:57.168 --> 11:58.668
<i> [tense music]</i>

11:58.770 --> 12:01.404
- I was robbed.
- Robbed?

12:01.506 --> 12:02.738
By who?

12:04.776 --> 12:06.842
Have you had anything to drink
this morning, Mister...

12:06.945 --> 12:10.012
<i> - I need to think,</i>
<i> or it's game over.</i>

12:10.114 --> 12:12.014
Oh, I'm sorry,
Spencer Hewitt.

12:13.217 --> 12:14.951
- Can you step out
of the car, please?

12:15.053 --> 12:19.822
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:19.924 --> 12:20.990
- Okay.

12:23.962 --> 12:25.394
- Put your hands
on the Buick, sir.

12:25.496 --> 12:27.263
Take off your glasses,
please.

12:36.541 --> 12:38.574
You gonna tell me
what happened to your face?

12:48.653 --> 12:50.820
- [sighs]

12:50.922 --> 12:53.489
Mm, morning Beckalíssama.

12:53.591 --> 12:54.890
- What are you doing?

12:54.993 --> 12:57.693
- Just eating breakfast.
I was starving.

12:57.795 --> 12:59.161
- You don't eat any of this.

12:59.263 --> 13:01.297
- Just felt like carpe-ing
the diem, you know.

13:01.399 --> 13:03.332
When I was a kid,
I used to come up here,

13:03.434 --> 13:05.401
and my aunt would make
this massive spread.

13:05.503 --> 13:08.337
And I don't know. I guess
I got inspired by the memory.

13:08.439 --> 13:10.172
It's easy to forget sometimes.

13:10.274 --> 13:11.807
You want to go to the mall?

13:11.909 --> 13:13.676
- Um...

13:13.778 --> 13:15.478
you haven't shopped retail
since the Steve Madden incident

13:15.580 --> 13:17.013
freshman year.
- I know. I know.

13:17.115 --> 13:18.714
I feel like slumming it,
and then we can get lunch.

13:18.816 --> 13:20.650
I am craving pizza
like a madwoman.

13:20.752 --> 13:22.084
And then we can top it off
with a matinee.

13:22.186 --> 13:23.753
What do you say?
- I don't know.

13:23.855 --> 13:25.154
It sounds like a lot.

13:25.256 --> 13:26.689
I'm kind of tired.

13:26.791 --> 13:28.224
- That's my fault.

13:28.326 --> 13:30.326
I've been a lot
to handle lately,

13:30.428 --> 13:31.761
and I want to make it
up to you.

13:31.863 --> 13:33.863
So why don't you eat
your breakfast

13:33.965 --> 13:37.199
and get dressed and then
let me spoil my best friend?

13:37.301 --> 13:38.934
Now eat up.

13:42.206 --> 13:43.706
- Just kids.

13:43.808 --> 13:45.574
They really kicked
the shit out of me, though.

13:45.677 --> 13:48.411
Took my wallet
and my wedding ring.

13:48.513 --> 13:51.280
- Not your watch, though.
- No.

13:51.382 --> 13:53.582
No, I got lucky, I guess.

13:53.685 --> 13:56.385
<i> Lucky he wouldn't know</i>
<i> an $80,000 Genevan timepiece</i>

13:56.487 --> 13:59.188
<i> if it slapped him in the dick.</i>
<i> Thanks, Benji.</i>

13:59.290 --> 14:01.757
Apparently it doesn't
take brains to be a criminal.

14:01.859 --> 14:03.259
- Just balls.

14:03.361 --> 14:04.927
<i> - Oh, if Opie's gonna</i>
<i> bone me,</i>

14:05.029 --> 14:06.962
<i> I wish he'd lube up</i>
<i> and get on with it.</i>

14:07.065 --> 14:09.031
- I'm gonna have
to go run your plate.

14:09.133 --> 14:10.866
Then I'll let you
get home to your wife.

14:10.968 --> 14:13.102
Must be nice to be married
to a doctor.

14:13.204 --> 14:14.370
- Sure is.

14:16.340 --> 14:18.441
You get out
on the water much, Officer?

14:20.511 --> 14:22.545
Yeah, you got the look.
I can tell.

14:22.647 --> 14:24.880
Listen, be our guest
next summer.

14:24.982 --> 14:27.249
The old man's bringing
the yacht up from Nantucket.

14:27.351 --> 14:29.218
- What model?

14:29.320 --> 14:31.554
- Azimut 62S.

14:31.656 --> 14:33.789
The "Guinevere."

14:33.891 --> 14:35.725
Quick little minx.

14:35.827 --> 14:38.494
<i> You see that?</i>
<i> Contempt.</i>

14:38.596 --> 14:40.830
<i> Opie just decided</i>
<i> I'm a rich tool</i>

14:40.932 --> 14:43.065
<i> and of no consequence</i>
<i> to the health and safety</i>

14:43.167 --> 14:44.633
<i> of his jurisdiction.</i>

14:44.736 --> 14:47.136
<i> He won't run my plates.</i>
- You know...

14:49.107 --> 14:51.474
Maybe you should just get home,
get some rest.

14:51.576 --> 14:53.409
<i> - No rest for the wicked.</i>

14:53.511 --> 14:55.311
<i> But I appreciate the concept.</i>

14:55.413 --> 14:56.712
Thank you so much.

14:56.814 --> 14:58.314
- Drive safe.
- [chuckles]

15:05.923 --> 15:08.457
[engine turning over]

15:08.559 --> 15:11.026
[engine revving]

15:11.129 --> 15:13.996
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

15:14.098 --> 15:21.137
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:25.443 --> 15:30.179
<i> I'm just here to be close by</i>
<i> if you need me.</i>

15:30.281 --> 15:35.384
<i> I don't trust Peach, Beck,</i>
<i> and neither should you.</i>

15:35.486 --> 15:38.020
<i> This place is a castle</i>

15:38.122 --> 15:41.824
<i> complete with wicked witch</i>
<i> and damsel in distress.</i>

15:41.926 --> 15:43.459
<i> Guess that makes me</i>
<i> your knight.</i>

15:43.561 --> 15:46.028
<i> For you, Beck, yes.</i>

15:46.130 --> 15:49.298
<i> [tense piano music]</i>

15:49.400 --> 15:51.400
<i> Oh, I wasn't planning</i>
<i> to break in,</i>

15:51.502 --> 15:54.370
<i> but if you're gonna leave</i>
<i> the back door wide open...</i>

15:54.472 --> 15:59.542
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:59.644 --> 16:03.345
<i> Okay. Nobody home.</i>

16:03.447 --> 16:06.081
<i> Oop, my head.</i>

16:06.184 --> 16:07.850
<i> [high-pitched ringing]</i>

16:07.952 --> 16:14.957
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:24.769 --> 16:27.136
<i> All in all,</i>
<i> I thought it'd be worse.</i>

16:27.238 --> 16:30.239
<i> [high-pitched ringing]</i>

16:33.277 --> 16:36.412
<i> I got a concussion once</i>
<i> playing soccer</i>

16:36.514 --> 16:39.014
<i> when I was 12.</i>
<i> Puked my brains out.</i>

16:39.116 --> 16:41.116
<i> Not fun</i>
<i> but nowhere near enough</i>

16:41.219 --> 16:42.852
<i> to keep me from my mission.</i>

16:42.954 --> 16:44.954
<i> If anything, it means</i>

16:45.056 --> 16:46.755
<i> I need to patch up.</i>

16:46.858 --> 16:48.691
<i> Focus.</i>

16:48.793 --> 16:50.492
<i> Get back in the game.</i>

16:50.595 --> 16:54.864
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:10.348 --> 17:13.449
- [sighs] Oh, wow.

17:13.551 --> 17:17.152
I'm so glad we got away
together like this, bunny.

17:17.889 --> 17:20.990
This place is adorable.

17:22.560 --> 17:24.293
I'm not leaving this bed

17:24.395 --> 17:26.462
for the next 48 hours.

17:26.564 --> 17:29.531
- [chuckles]
- You in?

17:29.634 --> 17:33.002
- Oh, I'm in.
- [laughing]

17:34.739 --> 17:36.972
<i> [moans]</i>
<i> - I love you, you know.</i>

18:12.977 --> 18:14.877
[door opens]

18:14.979 --> 18:17.546
- The spirit of the '90s
is alive in Greenwich.

18:17.648 --> 18:19.448
I can't wait to see
that dress on you.

18:19.550 --> 18:21.383
You have to try it on.

18:21.485 --> 18:24.153
<i> - It's so cold.</i>
<i> I think I'm gonna take a bath.</i>

18:24.255 --> 18:26.221
<i> - Oh, use the one</i>
<i> in the master.</i>

18:26.324 --> 18:28.357
It has well-placed jets.

18:30.795 --> 18:32.294
- I like the claw-foot tub.

18:32.396 --> 18:34.530
- Of course you do,
'cause you're classy.

18:34.632 --> 18:37.032
Cocktail?
I'll get you one.

18:37.134 --> 18:44.139
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:58.155 --> 19:01.156
[water running]

19:04.428 --> 19:11.433
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:22.847 --> 19:26.048
<i> - I want to give you a life</i>
<i> this grand someday.</i>

19:26.150 --> 19:27.750
<i> God knows you deserve it.</i>
<i> - Darling.</i>

19:27.852 --> 19:29.251
<i>I made you a Negroni.</i>

19:29.353 --> 19:31.186
<i> - Minus the unwanted pressure</i>

19:31.288 --> 19:33.422
<i> from an obviously unstable</i>
<i> obsessed person, of course.</i>

19:37.061 --> 19:40.295
<i> My hatred for Peach has</i>
<i> practically become sentient.</i>

19:40.398 --> 19:43.132
- Now, take your time
and relax, okay?

19:43.234 --> 19:44.933
I've got a surprise for you
when you get out.

19:45.036 --> 19:47.436
Oh, and don't forget to use
that geothermal mud mask.

19:47.538 --> 19:49.238
It is life-changing.
- Mm.

19:49.340 --> 19:50.639
- Cheers.
- Thanks.

19:56.147 --> 20:03.152
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:12.763 --> 20:14.663
<i> - Look at that.</i>

20:14.765 --> 20:18.133
<i> How dare she invade</i>
<i> your privacy like that?</i>

20:18.235 --> 20:19.601
<i> It's perverse.</i>

20:19.703 --> 20:21.503
<i> God, I have to pee.</i>

20:21.605 --> 20:24.473
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

20:24.575 --> 20:31.580
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:33.551 --> 20:36.552
[urine trickling]

20:42.593 --> 20:44.693
<i> I'll double back for that.</i>

20:46.397 --> 20:50.065
<i> How long is she going</i>
<i> to stand there staring at you?</i>

21:00.211 --> 21:01.343
[door slams]

21:03.647 --> 21:06.515
<i> [ominous music]</i>

21:06.617 --> 21:13.622
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:43.654 --> 21:44.920
- Hello?

21:46.157 --> 21:47.623
Anyone here?

21:50.461 --> 21:52.995
[doorbell rings]

21:53.097 --> 21:54.196
[sighs]

21:54.298 --> 21:56.431
<i> - Who is that?</i>
- Uh...

21:56.534 --> 21:58.467
it's the surprise.

22:00.704 --> 22:02.938
<i> - She has a gun, Beck.</i>

22:03.040 --> 22:06.508
<i> She's not in her right mind,</i>
<i> and you know it.</i>

22:06.610 --> 22:08.477
<i> I have to do something.</i>

22:08.579 --> 22:11.580
<i> 80% of gun accidents happen</i>
<i> in the home.</i>

22:18.122 --> 22:22.724
<i> Why is Peach dressing you up</i>
<i> like a doll?</i>

22:22.826 --> 22:25.961
- Okay, I'm wearing
this ridiculous thing.

22:26.063 --> 22:27.863
What's my surprise?

22:30.067 --> 22:32.434
Oh, my God, Raj.

22:32.536 --> 22:34.870
- Hey, gorgeous.
Long time, no see.

22:34.972 --> 22:37.105
- [chuckles]

22:37.208 --> 22:39.274
- Can't wait to catch up, doll.

22:45.861 --> 22:48.495
[ukulele strumming]

22:48.597 --> 22:50.997
[cell phone buzzing]

22:53.035 --> 22:55.569
- I thought we said no phones.

22:55.671 --> 22:56.636
- Sorry.

22:57.839 --> 22:59.339
It's just my brother.

22:59.441 --> 23:00.907
All right.

23:01.009 --> 23:02.309
Let's duet.

23:04.713 --> 23:06.446
- You know any Sabbath?

23:06.548 --> 23:08.982
- Uh...
[fast strumming]

23:09.084 --> 23:10.784
[laughs]

23:10.886 --> 23:13.019
<i> [high-pitched ringing]</i>

23:18.594 --> 23:21.761
<i> - It's funny what sticks</i>
<i> in your brain.</i>

23:21.863 --> 23:24.297
<i> Sounds, a bit of song...</i>

23:24.399 --> 23:25.932
- Give us one second, Raj.

23:26.034 --> 23:28.468
<i> - And now, I fear,</i>
<i> this chucklehead's voice</i>

23:28.570 --> 23:29.970
<i> calling you gorgeous.</i>

23:30.072 --> 23:32.005
<i> I knew Peach</i>
<i> was an instigator,</i>

23:32.107 --> 23:34.841
<i> and this is when her trap</i>
<i> starts closing in.</i>

23:34.943 --> 23:36.376
- What the hell
is he doing here?

23:36.478 --> 23:38.011
- I thought it'd be fun.

23:38.113 --> 23:39.212
- What happened to you
not wanting

23:39.314 --> 23:41.014
to be around male energy?

23:41.116 --> 23:42.649
- I feel much better now.

23:42.751 --> 23:44.150
- Well, that makes one of us.

23:44.253 --> 23:46.620
- You're still mad at me.
I get that.

23:46.722 --> 23:47.954
- Do you?

23:48.056 --> 23:49.956
- I said your poetry
was self-absorbed.

23:50.058 --> 23:52.459
And I'm sorry
my words hurt, but I--

23:52.561 --> 23:53.860
- But?

23:53.962 --> 23:55.161
- Hear me out.

23:55.264 --> 23:56.830
[sighs]

23:56.932 --> 23:59.866
You are one of the most
talented people I know.

23:59.968 --> 24:02.168
And I hate to see you
conforming to a system

24:02.271 --> 24:04.704
that is designed
to crush individuality.

24:04.806 --> 24:06.539
If you want to be
a great writer,

24:06.642 --> 24:07.974
you have to get out there

24:08.076 --> 24:09.676
and live a life
worth writing about.

24:09.778 --> 24:11.144
- What do you want me
to do, Peach,

24:11.246 --> 24:12.912
live off the land?

24:13.015 --> 24:16.483
- [sighs] Cousin Inez finally
vacated the Paris flat.

24:16.585 --> 24:18.218
I talked to my dad.

24:18.320 --> 24:19.986
He said I could have it
and oversee the renovation.

24:20.088 --> 24:22.355
She had a pet ocelot.
There was damage.

24:22.457 --> 24:25.158
- Wait, you're moving to Paris?

24:25.260 --> 24:28.128
- We are moving
to Paris,<i> chérie.</i>

24:31.967 --> 24:34.534
- Peach, this is crazy. I--

24:34.636 --> 24:36.936
- I don't need an answer
right now.

24:37.039 --> 24:40.206
Relax. I just want you
to trip on it.

24:40.309 --> 24:42.709
- Hence Raj.
- Look.

24:42.811 --> 24:45.812
Paris could be a new beginning
for the both of us.

24:47.683 --> 24:49.749
Say you'll think about it.

24:49.851 --> 24:51.985
<i> - Don't do it.</i>

24:53.789 --> 24:54.821
- Okay.

24:56.291 --> 24:57.791
- Okay.

25:03.732 --> 25:07.400
<i> [mellow pop music]</i>

25:07.502 --> 25:09.269
- Ladies first.
- [sighs]

25:09.371 --> 25:10.770
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:10.872 --> 25:13.306
- Okay, to old friends

25:13.408 --> 25:15.041
and new experiences.

25:15.143 --> 25:16.476
- Cheers.

25:16.578 --> 25:20.747
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:20.849 --> 25:23.049
I haven't been
this relaxed in weeks.

25:23.151 --> 25:25.385
- Wait until that baby
kicks in.

25:25.487 --> 25:29.322
- So what did we take
with utter blind trust in you?

25:29.424 --> 25:33.593
- Pure MDMA, slightest dash
of organically sourced opium.

25:33.695 --> 25:35.428
- Well, way to go,
Walter White.

25:35.530 --> 25:37.630
<i> - I could never blame you,</i>
<i> Beck, not even for this.</i>

25:37.733 --> 25:39.399
<i> Peach is a master at her game.</i>

25:39.501 --> 25:42.302
<i> Step one, get you alone</i>
<i> in a secluded house.</i>

25:42.404 --> 25:45.105
<i> Step two, invite</i>
<i> this Raj person over,</i>

25:45.207 --> 25:47.207
<i> fill you with drugs,</i>
<i> and get you to cheat on me.</i>

25:47.309 --> 25:50.377
<i> Step three, steal you away</i>
<i> to Paris forever.</i>

25:54.082 --> 25:55.682
<i> Had to get everything</i>
<i> put away</i>

25:55.784 --> 25:58.284
<i> and tidy for Raj,</i>
<i> didn't you?</i>

25:58.387 --> 26:00.086
<i> I need to find that gun.</i>

26:00.188 --> 26:01.254
[piano note plays]

26:03.225 --> 26:05.992
- So what have you
been up to, Raj?

26:06.094 --> 26:08.294
- Well, you know, finishing up
medical school.

26:08.397 --> 26:10.163
Wham, bam, get it done.

26:10.265 --> 26:12.465
What have you been up to,
Guinevere Beck?

26:12.567 --> 26:13.600
Still writing?

26:13.702 --> 26:14.968
- You should read her poetry.

26:15.070 --> 26:16.336
It's beguiling.

26:16.438 --> 26:19.272
- Honestly, I don't know
what I'm gonna do.

26:19.374 --> 26:22.342
I thought I did, but lately
it hasn't been so clear.

26:22.444 --> 26:29.449
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:32.154 --> 26:33.820
<i> - It was here.</i>

26:33.922 --> 26:35.822
- I bet you're doing better
than you think you are.

26:35.924 --> 26:37.857
- Beck's just having
a little writer's block.

26:37.959 --> 26:40.627
It'll pass.
- I want to write a book

26:40.729 --> 26:43.163
about an injured soul,

26:43.265 --> 26:45.665
someone who doesn't feel like
they have a place in the world

26:45.767 --> 26:48.701
as we know it,
someone on the outside.

26:48.804 --> 26:50.403
- You should write
about my stalker.

26:50.505 --> 26:51.604
- [chuckles]

26:53.508 --> 26:55.508
[sighs] I love that.

26:55.610 --> 26:57.310
- I know you do.

27:02.150 --> 27:03.850
<i> - Peach is playing with me.</i>

27:03.952 --> 27:06.653
<i> She knows I'm here.</i>
<i> This is all a trap.</i>

27:06.755 --> 27:07.921
I sound crazy.

27:08.023 --> 27:09.522
<i> Head injury. The car.</i>

27:09.624 --> 27:11.024
<i> I might be</i>
<i> a little crazy right now.</i>

27:11.126 --> 27:13.059
No, no, no, no, no.
No, I'm not.

27:13.161 --> 27:15.829
<i> I'm not. This is real.</i>
<i> She had a gun somewhere.</i>

27:15.931 --> 27:17.931
<i> You're not safe.</i>

27:20.602 --> 27:23.069
- Raj, feel how soft
this feels.

27:23.171 --> 27:30.176
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:31.446 --> 27:33.680
- It is soft.

27:33.782 --> 27:36.115
- You smell good.

27:36.218 --> 27:37.684
- So do you.

27:37.786 --> 27:44.691
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:44.793 --> 27:47.794
<i> [high-pitched ringing]</i>

27:59.207 --> 28:01.808
- [giggling]

28:03.478 --> 28:05.745
Platonic massage train.

28:05.847 --> 28:07.113
I call front.

28:07.215 --> 28:09.382
- I need a sec.
I'm spinning out.

28:09.484 --> 28:11.317
- I got you.

28:17.359 --> 28:20.059
<i> - Is this rock bottom?</i>

28:20.161 --> 28:23.396
<i> Because it sure feels like it.</i>
- [moaning]

28:23.498 --> 28:24.998
<i> - Do you see now?</i>

28:25.100 --> 28:28.334
<i> I would do anything</i>
<i> for you, Beck.</i>

28:28.436 --> 28:31.905
<i> [high-pitched ringing]</i>

28:32.007 --> 28:34.507
<i> I don't know why Candace</i>
<i> followed me here.</i>

28:34.609 --> 28:38.745
<i> It's like I hit my head</i>
<i> and bad memories jolted loose.</i>

28:38.847 --> 28:42.749
<i> It's a coincidence, Beck.</i>
<i> You and she are nothing alike.</i>

28:42.851 --> 28:46.286
<i> Nothing. Or maybe you are.</i>

28:46.388 --> 28:48.354
<i> I can't tell anymore.</i>

28:48.456 --> 28:50.290
- [chuckles]
- How good does that feel?

28:50.392 --> 28:52.492
- Oh, my gosh.

28:54.029 --> 28:55.595
[sighs]

28:55.697 --> 28:58.631
<i> - Beck, run.</i>
<i> [high-pitched ringing]</i>

28:58.733 --> 29:00.466
<i> Can't you feel</i>
<i> what she's doing,</i>

29:00.569 --> 29:02.168
<i> what she wants?</i>

29:04.606 --> 29:06.873
<i> Don't you want to run?</i>

29:11.613 --> 29:13.880
<i> Maybe you don't.</i>

29:16.551 --> 29:19.786
- Okay. Way too far.

29:19.888 --> 29:21.487
<i> - Yes.</i>
- I said

29:21.590 --> 29:24.023
platonic massage train.
- Oh, Beck.

29:24.125 --> 29:25.792
You're always so skittish.

29:25.894 --> 29:30.029
- Yeah, platonic means friends
just being friendly.

29:30.131 --> 29:32.732
- Yeah, well,
I have a boyfriend.

29:32.834 --> 29:36.469
<i> - Yes, you do,</i>
<i> my perfect girl.</i>

29:36.571 --> 29:38.338
- Well, I don't.

29:38.440 --> 29:40.707
- Me neither.
- I think I need to dance.

29:40.809 --> 29:42.041
I'm gonna go dance.

29:42.143 --> 29:44.877
<i> - I feel bad for Peach,</i>
<i> really.</i>

29:44.980 --> 29:47.714
<i> It's tragic not to be able</i>
<i> to show who you really are,</i>

29:47.816 --> 29:49.215
<i> and it's turned her poisonous.</i>

29:49.317 --> 29:51.184
- Oh, that feels good.

29:51.286 --> 29:53.252
Oh, okay, no.

29:53.355 --> 29:55.254
Yeah, a little lower.
<i> - Oh, my.</i>

29:55.357 --> 29:57.890
<i> I bet Harry never</i>
<i> had to do this for Sally.</i>

29:57.993 --> 29:59.392
- Yeah, mm.
Mm-hmm.

29:59.494 --> 30:01.361
[cell phone buzzing]
Okay.

30:01.463 --> 30:04.664
[moans]
I have something.

30:04.766 --> 30:09.335
<i> - Hi.</i>
- [moaning]

30:09.437 --> 30:11.004
Hold on.
<i> - Hi.</i>

30:11.106 --> 30:13.506
- [moaning]

30:13.608 --> 30:14.874
<i> - I think I'm done</i>
<i> being mad at you now.</i>

30:14.976 --> 30:16.275
- Okay.

30:17.212 --> 30:19.879
[cell phone dings]

30:19.981 --> 30:21.547
<i> - Okay, be right back,</i>

30:21.650 --> 30:23.950
<i> just gonna climb in</i>
<i> from off this ledge.</i>

30:24.052 --> 30:25.518
<i> - You're cute.</i>

30:27.689 --> 30:29.622
<i> - I really am sorry.</i>

30:31.526 --> 30:34.127
<i> - I know...Joe?</i>

30:35.363 --> 30:37.697
<i> - Yes?</i>

30:37.799 --> 30:41.300
<i> - I don't want to go to Paris.</i>

30:41.403 --> 30:44.604
<i> - Note to self: no Paris.</i>

30:44.706 --> 30:46.105
- Okay.

30:46.207 --> 30:48.307
I know he's down here
somewhere.

30:48.410 --> 30:49.642
Um...

30:51.246 --> 30:53.146
I swear it was here.
I just used it.

30:53.248 --> 30:54.313
Oh.

30:54.416 --> 30:55.715
Okay.

30:57.052 --> 30:59.118
<i> - Another thing</i>
<i> I keep learning...</i>

30:59.220 --> 31:00.186
- Yes.

31:02.157 --> 31:03.890
<i> - Things can always get worse.</i>

31:03.992 --> 31:05.324
- All right, you want this?

31:05.427 --> 31:06.926
- I don't not want it.

31:07.028 --> 31:09.128
- Okay. Here he comes.
Big daddy.

31:09.230 --> 31:12.131
<i> - Oh, Beck.</i>
<i> I'm so boned.</i>

31:12.233 --> 31:15.201
<i> But not as boned as Raj</i>
<i> is about to be.</i>

31:15.303 --> 31:17.704
- Oh, God, that's interesting.

31:21.935 --> 31:24.836
<i> [mellow pop music]</i>

31:24.938 --> 31:27.906
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:28.008 --> 31:31.276
<i> - [groans]</i>
<i> I feel like Colonel Kurtz.</i>

31:31.378 --> 31:33.611
<i> An entire night of listening</i>
<i> to Peach Salinger</i>

31:33.714 --> 31:37.482
<i> over and over and over</i>
<i> and over and over and over.</i>

31:37.584 --> 31:41.286
<i> The horror. One thing got me</i>
<i> through the long night.</i>

31:41.388 --> 31:42.821
<i> My mantra.</i>

31:42.923 --> 31:45.256
<i> You miss me.</i>

31:45.359 --> 31:48.226
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

31:48.328 --> 31:55.333
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:00.140 --> 32:01.506
- Packed already?

32:01.608 --> 32:02.841
We don't leave
for another two days.

32:02.943 --> 32:04.342
- Yeah, about that.

32:04.444 --> 32:06.544
I'm going back to the city.

32:06.646 --> 32:08.113
- Good. Great.

32:08.215 --> 32:10.448
You have stuff to wrap up
and then Paris.

32:11.451 --> 32:13.485
- Okay, I've thought about it.

32:13.587 --> 32:17.055
Thank you, but I belong
in New York.

32:17.157 --> 32:19.991
I'm not ready to give up yet.

32:20.093 --> 32:21.526
- Give up?

32:21.628 --> 32:23.828
I'm asking you to take
a leap of faith.

32:23.930 --> 32:25.230
I mean, do you want
to be an artist

32:25.332 --> 32:26.965
or an institutionalized cliché?

32:27.067 --> 32:29.200
- You're asking me
to quit my MFA.

32:29.302 --> 32:32.137
Leave New York, my friends,
my relationship--

32:32.239 --> 32:34.906
- Oh, good God, you've known
him for, like, five seconds.

32:35.008 --> 32:36.975
- I'm just saying that--
- Okay, do yourself a favor.

32:37.077 --> 32:39.844
Have some self-esteem and lose
the creepy retail loser.

32:39.946 --> 32:41.746
- Do we have to go there?
- I'm just being real.

32:41.848 --> 32:43.415
- Okay, you want to be real?

32:43.517 --> 32:45.116
What was that last night?

32:46.186 --> 32:48.553
- What was what?
- You kissed me.

32:50.023 --> 32:51.322
- [chuckles]

32:51.425 --> 32:53.324
We were all rolling.

32:55.295 --> 32:56.828
You always do this.

32:56.930 --> 32:59.397
- What? What do I do?
- Drama out of nothing.

32:59.499 --> 33:01.533
I mean, you were really high.

33:01.635 --> 33:03.668
You were leaning into me
and, quite frankly,

33:03.770 --> 33:05.370
being very initiating.
- What?

33:05.472 --> 33:08.239
- And I went with it because,
whatever, it was a party.

33:08.341 --> 33:10.275
<i> I didn't want it to be weird</i>
<i> because I'm your friend,</i>

33:10.377 --> 33:12.444
<i> and that's what friends do.</i>
<i> - That is not what happened.</i>

33:12.546 --> 33:14.612
- Jesus Christ, Beck.
Be an adult, okay?

33:14.714 --> 33:16.347
Take a little responsibility.
- Can we slow down?

33:16.450 --> 33:18.249
I'm just saying...

33:18.351 --> 33:22.053
Shit, I'm trying to say
I am your friend.

33:22.155 --> 33:24.088
So if--
- Jesus Christ.

33:24.191 --> 33:27.358
- I know your family.
I know how they are.

33:27.461 --> 33:30.462
I know they wouldn't be okay--
- No. No. I'm sorry.

33:30.564 --> 33:32.397
You have issues, okay?

33:32.499 --> 33:34.299
Don't make
your desperate unending need

33:34.401 --> 33:35.900
for attention about me.

33:36.002 --> 33:37.969
This entire conversation
is insane.

33:38.071 --> 33:41.272
- Okay, can we back up
for one second?

33:41.374 --> 33:43.374
I am not attacking you.

33:43.477 --> 33:45.410
I came here
to take care of you.

33:45.512 --> 33:47.979
- Of me?
Oh, that's rich.

33:48.081 --> 33:50.882
It really is.
- God, Peach, you know,

33:50.984 --> 33:53.418
Joe sees it too.
He's been trying to tell me.

33:53.520 --> 33:56.955
- [chuckles dully]
Course Joe's behind this.

33:57.057 --> 33:59.724
Joe is trash.

33:59.826 --> 34:01.726
Joe is nothing.

34:01.828 --> 34:03.428
You're my family.

34:03.530 --> 34:06.130
I'd die for you.
Would he?

34:06.233 --> 34:08.533
<i> - In a heartbeat.</i>

34:10.871 --> 34:12.237
- I need a break.

34:12.339 --> 34:13.738
- And what?

34:13.840 --> 34:16.107
Go slum it with
the proletariat?

34:16.209 --> 34:18.076
[scoffs] I give you a week.

34:18.178 --> 34:19.744
- My Uber's here.

34:21.114 --> 34:22.146
- So what?

34:22.249 --> 34:23.314
You're just going to abandon me

34:23.416 --> 34:24.649
when I need you the most?

34:24.751 --> 34:26.518
What about my stalker?

34:26.620 --> 34:29.254
- I'll text you the number
of a private security company.

34:29.356 --> 34:30.755
Call them.

34:30.857 --> 34:33.424
- [huffs]
I can't believe you.

34:33.527 --> 34:36.094
After all I do for you.

34:36.196 --> 34:38.263
You just use people.

34:58.118 --> 34:59.984
<i> - You are good.</i>

35:00.086 --> 35:01.653
<i> Beck, you're medicine.</i>

35:01.755 --> 35:03.721
<i> You are the antidote</i>
<i> for liars,</i>

35:03.823 --> 35:06.190
<i> and you make cheating</i>
<i> a distant memory.</i>

35:06.293 --> 35:08.793
<i> And right now,</i>
<i> I love you so much.</i>

35:08.895 --> 35:11.362
<i> The ringing in my head is</i>
<i> [singsongy] music.</i>

35:11.464 --> 35:13.231
- Hey!

35:13.333 --> 35:14.666
Give me my phone.

35:14.768 --> 35:17.502
<i> [high-pitched ringing]</i>

35:17.604 --> 35:20.705
- I don't have your stupid--
- I'm not cheating on you.

35:20.807 --> 35:22.507
He's an A&R guy.

35:22.609 --> 35:25.343
I have to seem available, okay?
It's just business.

35:25.445 --> 35:27.345
- Business.
We've been through this.

35:27.447 --> 35:29.847
- Yeah, we sure have.

35:29.950 --> 35:31.516
- You're lying.

35:31.618 --> 35:33.051
You cheated on me.

35:33.153 --> 35:35.420
You broke my heart, Candace.
I let you go.

35:35.522 --> 35:36.854
Isn't that enough?

35:36.957 --> 35:38.389
- There's something wrong
with you.

35:38.491 --> 35:40.558
I thought some time away
would mellow you out.

35:40.660 --> 35:42.594
But you're jealous.
You're paranoid.

35:42.696 --> 35:44.028
You need help!

35:44.130 --> 35:45.330
Give--

35:48.635 --> 35:49.667
- Joseph.

35:49.769 --> 35:50.768
[blow lands]

36:03.141 --> 36:05.208
- Why are you
in my house, Joseph?

36:05.310 --> 36:07.210
<i> - Oh, I should have shot</i>
<i> this medusa</i>

36:07.312 --> 36:09.112
<i> when I had the chance.</i>

36:09.214 --> 36:11.448
Peach, put the gun down.
I can explain.

36:11.550 --> 36:13.116
- This is breaking
and entering.

36:13.218 --> 36:15.552
I'd be totally within my rights
to shoot you right now.

36:15.654 --> 36:18.822
- I...I'm here picking up Beck.

36:18.924 --> 36:21.558
- Beck's in an Uber.
What are you doing here?

36:23.562 --> 36:25.862
My God.

36:25.964 --> 36:27.664
You.

36:27.766 --> 36:29.199
- What?

36:30.002 --> 36:31.468
- You're my stalker.

36:31.570 --> 36:33.803
Aw, I knew something
was off about you,

36:33.906 --> 36:35.505
and I was right.

36:35.607 --> 36:37.641
How long have you been
obsessed with me?

36:37.743 --> 36:39.142
- [chuckling]
- Oh, don't deny it,

36:39.244 --> 36:40.644
you little shit.

36:40.746 --> 36:43.179
You stole my "Ozma,"
you stole my laptop,

36:43.282 --> 36:44.547
and at this point,

36:44.650 --> 36:46.182
I'm convinced you
attacked me in the park.

36:46.285 --> 36:49.085
- Why--wait, why
would I attack you

36:49.187 --> 36:50.487
if I'm so obsessed
with you?

36:50.589 --> 36:52.055
- I don't know how
your twisted mind works.

36:52.157 --> 36:53.356
'Cause you're sick?

36:53.458 --> 36:55.158
- You couldn't be more wrong.

36:55.260 --> 36:56.192
Sorry.
- Oh, really?

36:56.295 --> 36:58.228
Then why are you here, Joseph?

36:58.330 --> 37:00.563
- Why are you here?

37:00.666 --> 37:02.666
Peach, why are you?

37:05.938 --> 37:08.038
- Beck.

37:08.140 --> 37:09.406
Oh.

37:09.508 --> 37:12.008
This is about Beck, isn't it?

37:12.110 --> 37:14.377
I know what you said to her.

37:14.479 --> 37:16.546
You got in her head.

37:16.648 --> 37:18.515
Because you can't stand
to share her

37:18.617 --> 37:20.784
with somebody so much better
than you.

37:20.886 --> 37:23.486
I mean, you were just trying
to get me out of the way.

37:23.588 --> 37:25.455
[chuckling] Oh, my God.

37:33.799 --> 37:36.299
Why are you wearing
Benji's watch?

37:39.304 --> 37:41.104
Why are you wearing
Benji's watch?

37:41.206 --> 37:42.472
- You're right.

37:42.574 --> 37:44.207
You're right.
I stole your laptop.

37:44.309 --> 37:45.775
I found all the files.

37:45.877 --> 37:48.645
The ones you keep
on your friends.

37:48.747 --> 37:51.381
The ones with
the naked pics of Beck.

37:51.483 --> 37:53.783
Now, is that for blackmail

37:53.885 --> 37:55.151
or personal use?

37:55.253 --> 37:57.220
It's an impressive collection.

37:57.322 --> 37:58.488
I made copies.

37:58.590 --> 38:00.223
Now, I have no plans to share,

38:00.325 --> 38:02.592
but if anything happens to me,
my associate, Paco,

38:02.694 --> 38:06.596
has been instructed
to publish all the files online

38:06.698 --> 38:09.432
and send a link
to your entire address book.

38:09.534 --> 38:12.635
And we can walk away from this.

38:12.738 --> 38:14.738
Peach, we can...

38:16.875 --> 38:18.808
We can--we can let it go.

38:20.912 --> 38:23.613
It never happened.
- And what?

38:23.715 --> 38:26.116
We can go back to New York
and pretend to be friends?

38:26.218 --> 38:27.851
- If you like.
- No.

38:27.953 --> 38:29.919
I don't want you near Beck.
You're dangerous.

38:30.022 --> 38:31.121
- I'm better for her
than you are.

38:31.223 --> 38:33.156
Take the ticket, Peach.

38:33.258 --> 38:34.991
Go to Paris.

38:35.093 --> 38:38.028
Clear your head.
Find a nice French girl.

38:38.130 --> 38:40.363
'Cause you know, deep down,
she's never gonna love you

38:40.465 --> 38:42.165
the way you love her.
- Stop saying that.

38:42.267 --> 38:44.434
- She's never gonna do it.
You can't have her.

38:44.536 --> 38:46.569
- Stop saying that!
[gunshot]

38:46.671 --> 38:51.374
<i> [tense music]</i>

38:51.476 --> 38:52.742
[gunshot]

38:52.844 --> 38:54.844
- [groaning]

38:58.250 --> 39:04.687
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:14.266 --> 39:15.932
- Joseph?

39:34.953 --> 39:37.620
[groaning, straining]

39:45.897 --> 39:46.896
[gunshot]

39:49.719 --> 39:52.119
<i> - Family, friends, lovers,</i>
<i> and all the rest,</i>

39:52.221 --> 39:54.154
<i> forgive me for this.</i>

39:54.256 --> 39:58.025
<i> But it's not like you can say</i>
<i> you didn't see this coming.</i>

39:58.127 --> 39:59.993
<i> I've always had</i>
<i> a complicated relationship</i>

40:00.096 --> 40:01.595
<i> with my own existence.</i>

40:01.697 --> 40:03.430
<i> [indistinct</i>
<i> police radio chatter]</i>

40:03.532 --> 40:05.332
<i> I was given</i>
<i> a second chance on life</i>

40:05.434 --> 40:08.368
<i> after the attack</i>
<i> in the park, and...</i>

40:08.471 --> 40:10.938
<i> I've decided not to take it.</i>

40:11.040 --> 40:12.706
<i> I thought I could change</i>

40:12.808 --> 40:15.809
<i> and, by changing myself,</i>
<i> alter the world around me.</i>

40:15.911 --> 40:19.379
<i> But change</i>
<i> is a fool's pipe dream.</i>

40:19.482 --> 40:21.949
<i> This world is ugly and crass.</i>

40:22.051 --> 40:24.118
<i> People lie, and people leave.</i>

40:24.220 --> 40:27.554
<i> And the beauty that does exist</i>
<i> is fleeting and insincere.</i>

40:27.656 --> 40:29.857
<i> Still, every now and again,</i>

40:29.959 --> 40:32.960
<i> someone comes along who will</i>
<i> make you believe in love.</i>

40:33.062 --> 40:35.295
<i> And if you find that person,</i>

40:35.397 --> 40:37.331
<i> don't let go.</i>

40:37.433 --> 40:40.968
<i> And maybe together, you can</i>
<i> keep the monsters at bay.</i>

40:41.070 --> 40:43.137
<i> I was never that lucky.</i>

40:43.239 --> 40:46.840
<i> So I'm ending things</i>
<i> on my own terms.</i>

40:46.942 --> 40:49.510
<i> both: Know that</i>
<i> I love you all</i>

40:49.612 --> 40:53.147
<i> and hope we'll meet again</i>
<i> on the cosmic highway.</i>

40:53.249 --> 40:54.648
<i> Stay amazing.</i>

40:54.750 --> 40:58.218
<i> Love, Peach Anais Salinger.</i>

41:00.156 --> 41:01.588
<i> - What could I do?</i>

41:01.690 --> 41:03.724
<i> She was never going</i>
<i> to let you go.</i>

41:03.826 --> 41:07.261
<i> - Dispatch to Nico.</i>
- Go ahead.

41:07.363 --> 41:08.862
<i> - Ran that plate</i>
<i> you asked for.</i>

41:08.964 --> 41:10.998
<i> Car's registered</i>
<i> to an Ivan Mooney.</i>

41:11.100 --> 41:13.734
<i> Address in Manhattan.</i>
- Stolen?

41:13.836 --> 41:16.203
<i> - No. Not reported, anyway.</i>

41:16.305 --> 41:17.538
- Thanks, Diane.

41:17.640 --> 41:20.541
[siren wailing]

41:20.643 --> 41:23.510
<i> [dark piano music]</i>

41:23.612 --> 41:30.617
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:46.235 --> 41:48.001
- Well...

41:48.103 --> 41:49.837
you said you owe me one.

41:53.175 --> 41:54.741
- You're lucky.

41:54.844 --> 41:57.311
The bullet only grazed you.

41:57.413 --> 41:59.913
- [chuckles]

42:00.015 --> 42:01.782
I feel lucky.

42:02.818 --> 42:03.917
- You want to talk about it?

42:04.019 --> 42:05.619
- Not really, no.

42:05.721 --> 42:07.154
If you don't mind.

42:07.256 --> 42:09.122
- Mm. A favor's a favor.

42:10.926 --> 42:12.559
[sighs]

42:12.661 --> 42:15.562
So I took your advice.

42:15.664 --> 42:17.564
I kicked Ron out.

42:17.666 --> 42:19.933
You were right.
People don't change.

42:20.035 --> 42:22.970
Besides, I didn't like the way
he was treating Paco.

42:23.072 --> 42:24.504
Kid needs a real
father figure in his life,

42:24.607 --> 42:26.573
not some drunken asshole,
you know?

42:26.675 --> 42:28.575
[cell phone dings]

42:36.986 --> 42:38.886
[cell phone dings]

42:42.958 --> 42:46.460
<i> - That was nearly a week ago.</i>

42:46.562 --> 42:48.295
<i> It's been a whirlwind</i>
<i> since then.</i>

42:48.397 --> 42:50.197
<i> I thought I'd have to explain</i>
<i> my wounds to you,</i>

42:50.299 --> 42:52.499
<i> but you didn't even notice.</i>

42:52.601 --> 42:55.435
<i> I suppose I can</i>
<i> forgive you for that,</i>

42:55.537 --> 42:58.305
<i> what with your best friend</i>
<i> dying and all.</i>

42:58.407 --> 43:00.374
<i> You did ask me to go</i>
<i> to the funeral with you,</i>

43:00.476 --> 43:02.542
<i> which I think</i>
<i> is a good sign.</i>

43:02.645 --> 43:04.211
<i> You need emotional support</i>
<i> right now,</i>

43:04.313 --> 43:06.213
<i> and that's my specialty.</i>

43:06.315 --> 43:08.448
So the fridge
is fully stocked.

43:08.550 --> 43:11.351
I grabbed a couple Xanax
off Annika,

43:11.453 --> 43:13.854
just in case.

43:13.956 --> 43:15.956
<i> You're going to get</i>
<i> through this.</i>

43:16.058 --> 43:17.858
<i> It'll take time.</i>

43:17.960 --> 43:19.893
<i> But I'll give you</i>
<i> as much time as you need.</i>

43:19.995 --> 43:21.795
<i> And I know</i>
<i> once the dust settles,</i>

43:21.897 --> 43:25.132
<i> you will find</i>
<i> you're better off without her.</i>

43:26.969 --> 43:28.902
<i> You might not ever</i>
<i> admit this, of course.</i>

43:29.004 --> 43:32.306
<i> But I'll know, and that will</i>
<i> be all the validation I need.</i>

43:32.408 --> 43:33.807
I'm gonna head out.

43:35.577 --> 43:37.778
Text me if you need anything,
okay?

43:42.551 --> 43:43.717
Okay.

43:47.489 --> 43:48.588
- Joe?

43:50.292 --> 43:51.391
- Yeah?

43:51.493 --> 43:53.827
- Can you stay?

44:00.636 --> 44:03.337
- I can stay
as long as you want.

44:03.439 --> 44:06.306
<i> [emotional music]</i>

44:06.408 --> 44:13.413
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
